So is there any document to help me learn how to debug at the executor? If anyone could solve the problem, could you tell me the way you debug at the executor?  Thanks very very much! @selvaganesang  @DaveBirdsall

i though your suggection, and it's considerate, but it may be complex to cover all circumstance
discuss two situations
1:
if mxosrvr starts successful, say passed N step, then for a long time , it failure, this failure is more than X mins, and should restart, then while restarting it failure for some reason , maybe network error or something else i'm not sure, and this failure maybe a 1 min failure, i think it should restart again, but conflict with the strategy .
2:
if mxosrvr starts successful, say passed N step, then for a long time , it failure, this failure is more than X mins, and should restart, then restart successful , then users connect to this mxosrvr and do query (just exec values (1);) for 100 times, then mxosrvr down for the code logic, and the interval may be a 1-5mins, this can't restart either, for conflict with the strategy.

my idea is use my strategy ,and set "dcs.server.startup.mxosrvr.user.program.restart.handler.retry.timeout.minutes" a smaller value.
but this is not enough, there still need add a timer strategy, that is restart the "never restart mxosrvr" regularly, maybe one or two times a day.
and i think i can add the timer strategy in another PR. so how do you think this?
I had modified and committed  as review

This is only modified for tscancode checking.
I can start another work for compiling with -Wformat -Werror

For case 1. If there is a failure while starting mxosrvr (after mxorvr has been active for long time), it should be restarted. Only when there are 6 failures within the last 5 minutes it shouldn't be restarted.

For case 2: X is from the last failure. If it is more than 5 mins away, then it should be started.

It is possible that I haven't explained my suggestion  correctly or it is misunderstood. Anyway, I will wait for others to weigh in their input. If there is no other input within reasonable time, I will merge this PR after you reduce the timeout minutes.

Your suggestion is wrong. I had already explained before
the method Cluster maybe set error to rc, may be not. because may fail when call new
so we must check the * rc is set or not. If I write as following, will rewrite the error set by Cluster method:
`if (! next_) {`
`* rc = EXE_NO_MEM_TO_EXEC;`
`return TRUE;`
`}`

In that case you are making an assumption that EXE_OK is 0

It should be  if (*rc == EXE_OK)  *rc = EXE_NO_MEM_TO_EXEC;

Hi @traflm. You don't include any output so I'm not sure what's failing.

In your git log and git diff steps, you need to say apache/release2.2 instead of apache/master. So your git log and git diff commands were likely showing a lot more stuff than you expected.

The git push command should be "git push apache HEAD:release2.2"

@svarnau, do you see any other issues?
